Argentine Stocks: Aluar, Banco Macro and Banco Santander Rio

-- B y   E d u a r d o   T h o m s o n
-- 
2011-12-02T17:07:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/argentine-stocks-aluar-banco-macro-and-banco-santander-rio.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 1:42 p.m. in Buenos
Aires.  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index rose 0.8 percent to 2,630.58.  Aluar Aluminio Argentino SAIC (ALUA)   rose 2.1 percent to
3.42 pesos, its third day of gains. The country’s largest
aluminum producer gained in line with the price of the base
metal in London.  Banco Macro SA (BMA)   gained 2.7 percent to 9.75 pesos.
Argentina’s largest lender by market share rose amid gains in
global stock markets following an unexpected drop in the U.S.
unemployment rate.  Banco Santander Rio SA (BRIO)   advanced 2.1 percent to
7.15 pesos. The unit of Spain’s Banco Santander SA rose in line
with the price of its controller in Madrid.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eduardo Thomson in Santiago at 
 ethomson1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
